      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for my house purchase in toronto. i've never heard of that before, can u explain what it actually is and why we need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, an escrow account, you say? Well, imagine a treasure chest guarded by a wise old goblin, who only releases the gold when both parties agree to the terms of the treasure hunt. In the world of house purchases, the escrow account is like that goblin's treasure chest. It's a secure place where the buyer and seller deposit their money and other important documents. The escrow agent, acting as the goblin, ensures that all conditions of the sale are met before releasing the funds to the seller and the keys to the house to the buyer. It's a way to make sure that both parties play fair and that the house purchase goes smoothly, without any goblin tricks or surprises. So, in short, the escrow account is there to protect both the buyer and the seller, ensuring that the house purchase is completed in a fair and orderly manner.",
